reviews_list: Rated 30 RATEDn  Vishwamitra is another vegetarian restaurant situated just opposite to bowring hospital near Sri Rama It has better ambiance than rama and unlike the 70s80s ambiance of the former it looks a bit newer with 80s90s ambiance  We used to go here when we had our posting at the bowring hospital and  we have tried almost all their tiffin items Idly pongal bisi bele bath rice bath are all good Cost is cheap though a bit higher than Ramas but still cheap when compared to other vegetarian restaurants in the citynnsrirelishesblogspotcom Rated 30 RATEDn  One of my most visited hotels around shivajinagar the place was good when it opened the udin vada on a Sunday morning was really good and was consistent now due to the change in management we got some stale vadas when I went there recently Price wise its economical compared to the other places around that place

reviews_list: Rated 40 RATEDn  This place gives amazing tea I had dum chai and bun maska both gave my morning a good start The only problem is is over priced but taste good Rated 40 RATEDn  Chai Kraft got my attention when they had something called Purple Tea A little digging told me that Purple Tea is a tea brewed from the Butterfly Pea flower which gives the purple colour As a little hangout spot for tea or coffee or snack or maggi I chose to go here with my close friend for their Purple teannOn this menu they have a Purple Classic Tea Purple Masala Tea Purple Virgin Mojito Purple Iced Tea and Blue Brew Tea Our choice was Purple Classic Tea and Purple Virgin MojitonnThe tea arrives first A clear brew of Purple coloured tea with a dash of ginger and lime it tastes like a lemon ginger tea with an added benefit of the butterfly pea brewnnThe Purple Virgin Mojito looks like a magical concoction with a strong brew of the purple flower soda lime and ice A cool drink for the hot summer As a person with weird taste I liked the mojitonnWith pocket friendly prices my next visit will be to try the other drinks on the Purple Menu Rated 30 RATEDn  well Tea  coffee are made using milk powder  im not really a big fan of Tea  coffee made out of milk powder the most favorable tea for many The Ginger is not available most of the times and had to settle for normal tea they also sell few pastry and snack items which are bit overpriced
